          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-1866 lfsck: FID-in-dirent and linkEA consistency",
        "message": "LU-1866 lfsck: FID-in-dirent and linkEA consistency\n\nIn LFSCK 1.5, we have implemented the following functionalities:\n\n1) Initial OI scrub to verify and rebuild OI mappings for server\n   local objects when the server mounts.\n\n2) Verify and rebuild FID-in-dirent, mainly for MDT file-level\n   backup/resotre.\n\n3) (Partly) verify and rebuild FID-in-LMA: if the FID-in-dirent\n   is valid but FID-in-LMA is missed, then the later one will be\n   repaired.\n\n4) Verify and rebuild linkEA: find out and repair crashed linkEA\n   entry; find out and remove invalid linkEA entry.\n\n5) Handle IGIF object upgrading, generate IGIF-in-LMA, and add\n   FID-in-dirent and generate IGIF-format linkEA.\n\n6) Find out missing name entries and add them back to namespace.\n\n7) (Partly) find out missed object and add it back to namespace:\n   if name entry exists, but related inode nlink count is zero,\n   then the inode nlink count will be repaired.\n\n8) Verify and correct object's nlink attribute.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <yong.fan@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I8b0d0e8bc0ea84f8a6765b0b87376e4e95446d60\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
